7.2 Bottom line
The Site Configuration Model:
•	governs both design and non-design site configuration
•	uses richer instantiated Design Configuration objects because the design zone has layered Family, Scheme, and Preset relationships
•	uses structured category objects for the non-design zone
•	establishes Family as the top-level design archetype that declares allowedSchemes
