•	stores the active state in Current Design Selection
•	defines operating logic through Design Rules
•	is logical, practical, and implementable by code generation tools

SECTION 8 — FAMILY AND SCHEME MEANING DEFINITIONS
8. Family and Scheme Meaning Definitions
Governing Interpretation Rule
Family and Scheme meaning definitions are governed interpretation layers used to constrain later palette, typography, spacing, and radius decisions. They do not directly assign raw design values. They define the allowed design character within which later presets and defaults must be selected. A preset is allowed for a Scheme only if its declared character is consistent with that Scheme's intended visual character and does not violate the Scheme's exclusion guidance, the accessibility constraints of the Website Specification, or the semantic token structure of this document. No Family or Scheme meaning definition may be interpreted as permission to introduce values, styling patterns, or design behaviors outside the governed configuration model.

Family Definitions
Family — Startup / Professional
Purpose: Business-facing websites that need to communicate credibility, capability, clarity, and modern execution.
Overall posture: professional, credible, disciplined, modern, structured, commercially serious
Palette tendency: restrained, balanced, professional — either cool-neutral, technical-neutral, or warm-professional depending on the Scheme
Typography tendency: modern and readable, credible in long-form reading, suitable for structured headings and explanatory content, not theatrical or novelty-driven
Spacing tendency: disciplined, clean, moderate to moderately relaxed
Radius tendency: minimal to softly controlled, not playful or exaggerated
Out-of-bounds: playful or whimsical visual language; highly ornamental styling; culturally rich or celebratory treatments; visual noise or excessive contrast
Allowed Schemes: Professional Cool • Modern Technical • Warm Professional

Family — Personal
Purpose: Personal, expert, author, or individual-identity websites where the person is central but the site remains credible and refined.
Overall posture: personal, thoughtful, refined, human, expressive within control, identity-forward without becoming chaotic
Palette tendency: calm, modern, or warm depending on the Scheme — more expressive than Startup / Professional, still controlled and elegant
Typography tendency: more editorial or identity-sensitive, strong readability for essays and profile content, enough personality to feel authored
Spacing tendency: moderate to relaxed, slightly more breathable than Startup / Professional where appropriate
Radius tendency: minimal to soft, should support warmth or modernity without becoming playful
Out-of-bounds: overly corporate stiffness; overly playful or youthful design that weakens credibility; decorative complexity that distracts from the individual's voice
Allowed Schemes: Personal Calm • Personal Modern • Personal Warm

Family — Nonprofit Cultural
Purpose: Cultural, arts, heritage, education, or community-centered nonprofit websites where tradition, community, and meaning matter as much as usability.
Overall posture: culturally rich, respectful, elegant, community-aware, welcoming, capable of representing events, knowledge, and tradition
Palette tendency: warm, heritage-aware, or celebratory depending on the Scheme — richer than the other Families, still governed and disciplined
Typography tendency: editorial, elegant, and readable; may carry more cultural or traditional sensibility; still practical for digital reading
Spacing tendency: moderate to relaxed; should allow content to breathe; should support event, educational, and narrative content
Radius tendency: soft to moderately soft, not harshly technical
Out-of-bounds: cold technical minimalism; loud commercial styling; novelty or playful treatments that trivialize the mission; hyper-corporate visual language
Allowed Schemes: Cultural Heritage • Cultural Celebration • Cultural Learning

Scheme Definitions
Scheme — Professional Cool
Parent Family: Startup / Professional
Primary use signal: Executive credibility and premium strategic seriousness.
Intended visual character: restrained, polished, premium, cool-neutral, serious, low ornament, executive and structured
Appropriate use cases: when the site should feel highly credible, thoughtful, disciplined, strategically mature, calm rather than energetic
Palette tendency: cool neutrals, restrained accent use, low saturation, premium contrast rather than loud contrast
Typography tendency: modern professional, structured, highly readable, slight editorial discipline acceptable; should not feel traditional or decorative
Spacing tendency: standard or moderately relaxed, clean section rhythm, no compressed density, no highly loose lifestyle spacing
Radius tendency: minimal preferred, soft allowed only if still disciplined
Preset fit guidance — Typography: professional, modern, credible, restrained
Preset fit guidance — Spacing: structured, disciplined, clean
Preset fit guidance — Radius: minimal, controlled, subtly softened at most
Preset exclusion guidance — Typography: not playful, romantic, highly traditional, or decorative
Preset exclusion guidance — Spacing: not loose, casual, or lifestyle-oriented
Preset exclusion guidance — Radius: not playful, exaggerated, or soft in a way that weakens executive discipline
Likely default posture: typography — most restrained professional-modern option; spacing — standard; radius — minimal

Scheme — Modern Technical
Parent Family: Startup / Professional
Primary use signal: Product and system clarity with digital-technical fluency.
Intended visual character: technical, modern, crisp, product-aware, structured, efficient, more digital than editorial
Appropriate use cases: when the site should feel digitally fluent, product-minded, capable of systems thinking, modern and implementation-oriented
Palette tendency: cleaner technical neutrals, sharper accent control, slightly stronger contrast than Professional Cool, no warm advisory feel
Typography tendency: modern, product-oriented, crisp, efficient, less editorial than other options
Spacing tendency: standard preferred, slightly tighter discipline acceptable, not expansive or lounge-like
Radius tendency: minimal preferred, soft only in limited measure
Preset fit guidance — Typography: technical, clean, modern, implementation-aware
Preset fit guidance — Spacing: efficient, disciplined, product-like
Preset fit guidance — Radius: minimal, exact, non-playful
Preset exclusion guidance: no heritage, warm editorial, or culturally expressive typography; no expansive or lounge-like spacing; no rounded or playful radius
Likely default posture: typography — most product-technical option; spacing — standard; radius — minimal

Scheme — Warm Professional
Parent Family: Startup / Professional
Primary use signal: Advisory warmth with premium business credibility.
Intended visual character: professional, warm, premium, human, advisory, structured but less cool than Professional Cool
Appropriate use cases: expert and approachable, premium but not cold, strategic and human, serious without appearing severe
Palette tendency: warmer neutrals, controlled warmth, softer contrast than Modern Technical, still credible and clean
Typography tendency: editorial-professional, modern but slightly warmer, suited to advisory or thought-leadership content
Spacing tendency: standard to relaxed, slightly more breathable than Modern Technical
Radius tendency: soft controlled radius is more acceptable here; minimal still possible but not required
Preset fit guidance: typography — warm, professional, editorial in a disciplined way; spacing — breathable, composed, premium; radius — soft controlled
Preset exclusion guidance: no coldly technical or culturally ceremonial typography; no tight product-like or loose lifestyle-like spacing; no exaggerated or playful radius
Likely default posture: typography — strongest editorial-professional option; spacing — relaxed if remaining disciplined; radius — soft or softly controlled

Scheme — Personal Calm
Parent Family: Personal
Primary use signal: Reflective personal voice and calm editorial presence.
