APPENDIX A — DESIGN PROFILE DEFINITIONS
Appendix A — Design Profile Definitions

A.1 Purpose of Appendix A
 This appendix defines the governed design profiles used by the Design Configuration portion of the Plenor Site Configuration Document.
 These design profiles are the semantic interpretation layer for Family and Scheme objects. They define the intended visual character of each Family and Scheme so that later palette selection, preset allow-list definition, default preset selection, and current design selection are constrained by governed meaning rather than ad hoc judgment.
 This appendix is subordinate to the governing rules in the main body of the Plenor Site Configuration Document. It does not replace Family, Scheme, Preset, Current Design Selection, or Design Rule objects. It constrains how those objects are instantiated and interpreted.
A.2 Governing interpretation rule
 Family and Scheme design profiles are governed interpretation layers used to constrain later palette, typography, spacing, and radius decisions. They do not directly assign raw design values. They define the allowed design character within which later presets and defaults must be selected.
 A preset is allowed for a Scheme only if its declared character is consistent with that Scheme’s intended visual character and does not violate the Scheme’s exclusion guidance, the accessibility constraints of the Website Specification, or the semantic token structure of the Site Configuration Document.
 No Family or Scheme design profile may be interpreted as permission to introduce values, styling patterns, or design behaviors outside the governed configuration model.
