APPENDIX B — DESIGN CONFIGURATION TEMPLATES
Appendix B — Design Configuration Templates
This appendix defines the normalized templates for the design configuration portion of the Site Configuration Model. These templates are authoritative. In the event of ambiguity between an instantiated object record and the declared template structure in this appendix, the declared template structure governs unless changed through governed revision.

B.1 Purpose
This appendix defines what design objects exist, what fields each may contain, which fields are required, and how allowed sets, defaults, and current selections work.

B.2 Object format rule
Each design object must follow its declared structure exactly. A field may not be added unless it belongs to that object's declared responsibility, is accepted as part of the governed model, and does not duplicate an already-governed responsibility elsewhere.

