APPENDIX C — NON-DESIGN CONFIGURATION TEMPLATES
Appendix C — Non-Design Configuration Templates
C.1 Purpose
This appendix defines the normalized templates for the non-design configuration portion of the Site Configuration Model. In the event of ambiguity between an instantiated object record and the declared template structure in this appendix, the declared template structure governs unless changed through governed revision.

C.2 Non-Design Configuration Object format rule
Each non-design configuration object must follow its declared structure exactly. A field may not be added unless it belongs to that object's declared responsibility, is accepted as part of the governed model, and does not duplicate an already-governed responsibility elsewhere.

C.3 Identity and Brand Configuration template
Object: Identity and Brand Configuration Object
Allowed fields: legalName, tradingName, tagline, contactEmail, contactPhone, mailingAddress, logo assets, favicon assets, footer identity text, policy ownership text, social profile references, copyright format.

C.4 Navigation Configuration template
Object: Navigation Configuration Object
Allowed fields: primary navigation labels, primary navigation order, Framework secondary navigation labels and order, Solutions secondary navigation labels and order, Insights secondary navigation labels and order, About secondary navigation labels and order, mobile secondary navigation pattern.

C.5 Content Ordering and Display Fallback Configuration template
Object: Content Ordering and Display Fallback Configuration Object
Allowed fields: homepage fallback ordering rule, ordering tiebreaker rule, minimum content state by homepage section, placeholder content by homepage section, FAQ placement governance.

C.6 Operational Configuration template
Object: Operational Configuration Object
Allowed fields: public content lifecycle status labels, inquiry workflow status labels, form field labels and helper text, inquiry success message, resource request message, response expectation text, date and time display format conventions, implementation-scope decisions.

C.7 SEO and Metadata Configuration template
Object: SEO and Metadata Configuration Object
Allowed fields: default metadata values by content type, canonical rules, robots rules, sitemap rules, structured-data mappings by content type, social sharing asset references by content type.

Field rules:
•	value entries are used for defaults
•	rule entries are used for canonical, robots, and sitemap behavior
•	mapping entries are used for structured-data assignment
•	asset entries are used for social sharing references

APPENDIX D — SHARED RULES AND VALUE SETS
Appendix D — Shared Rules and Value Sets
D.1 Status set
The governed status set for current-phase configuration objects is:
Status	Meaning
Draft	Being defined; not yet approved for use
Approved	Approved and available for use
Deprecated	No longer recommended; may not be newly selected once deprecated; must be replaced before removal
Deferred	Intentionally excluded from the current phase; must be explicitly marked
Not Used in Current Phase	Structurally defined but not active in the current phase; must be explicitly marked

D.2 Configurability classes
Class	Meaning
Fixed	Set by governance; may not be changed without governed revision
Selectable	May be changed to another approved option within the governed allowed set
Override Allowed	Has a governed default but may be overridden within approved boundaries
System Managed	Managed by the platform or CMS within governed constraints

D.3 Entry types
Entry Type	Used For
Allowed Set Entry	Defining which values are permitted within an allowed set
Current Selection Entry	Recording which value is currently active
Default Mapping Entry	Recording the default value before any override or selection
Rule Entry	Defining governing logic
Value Entry	Defining a specific governed value
Asset Entry	Referencing a governed asset
Mapping Entry	Defining a correspondence between two governed sets

D.4 Governing interpretation rule
Where there is ambiguity between an instantiated object record and the declared template structure in the appendices, the declared template structure governs unless changed through governed revision.

D.5 Bottom line
The appendices define the formal structural templates of the Site Configuration Model. Once instantiated with actual values, those instantiated appendices can become direct structured inputs for spreadsheet-based configuration, CMS seeding, JSON or YAML transformation, or code generation workflows.

